layout: base.njk
permalink: /about/index.html
---

<style>
  .about-section {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
  }

  .about-section h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.65rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
  }

  .about-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-actions a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 2.75rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .about-actions a:hover,
  .about-actions a:focus-visible {
    background: #fff;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 0.16em;
  }

  .about-section ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .about-section h3 sup {
    font-size: small;
  }

  #about-text-p1 {
    text-indent: 2rem;
  }

  .about-footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: smaller;
  }
</style>

<article aria-labelledby="about-title">
  <header class="meditation-header">
    <h2 id="about-title" class="meditation-header-title">{{ site.aboutTitle }}</h2>
  </header>

  <div class="prose">
    <p id="about-text-p1">
      Discover inspiration &amp; daily encouragement with this accessible site, offering <cite>The Language of Letting Go</cite> — Melody Beattie's meditations on codependency, recovery, self-care, boundaries, and the steady practice of letting life unfold.
    </p>
    <p>
      The meditation text is by Melody Beattie. This web companion was built to make the readings easier to revisit online; the underlying writing remains the work of its original author and publisher.
    </p>
    <p>
      The book <cite>The Language of Letting Go</cite> can be purchased <a href="https://www.amazon.com.au/Language-Letting-Meditation-Meditations-Codependents/dp/0894866370" target="_blank" rel="noopener">from Amazon</a>.
    </p>

    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="about-dedication">
      <h3 id="about-dedication">Dedication <sup><a href="#fn1" id="ref1">1</a></sup></h3>
        {% quote "Melody Beattie" %}
          <p>For her help in writing this book, I acknowledge and thank Rebecca Post, my editor at Hazelden. This book is dedicated to</p>
          <ul>
            <li>God</li>
            <li>The readers of <em>Codependent No More</em> and <em>Beyond Codependency</em></li>
            <li>And my friend, Louie</li>
          </ul>
        {% endquote %}
    </section>

    <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="about-intro">
      <h3 id="about-intro">Introduction <sup><a href="#fn2" id="ref2">2</a></sup></h3>
        {% quote "Melody" %}
          <p>This is a book of meditations. It is designed to help you spend a few moments each day remembering what you know.</p>
          <p>I have touched on principles from <em>Codependent No More</em> and <em>Beyond Codependency</em>. I've also included some new thoughts and ideas.</p>
          <p>It is a book to help you feel good and assist you in the process of self-care and recovery.</p>
          <p>Thanks for the support, encouragement, and success you've given me. I hope I have given you a gift in return too.</p>
        {% endquote %}
    </section>
  </div>

  <footer class="about-footer">
    <ol>
      <li id="fn1">
        The dedication text is a verbatim copy from the book <cite>The Language of Letting Go</cite>.
        <sup><a href="#ref1" title="Jump back to reference">↩</a></sup>
      </li>
      <li id="fn2">
        The introduction text is a verbatim copy from the book <cite>The Language of Letting Go</cite>.
        <sup><a href="#ref2" title="Jump back to reference">↩</a></sup>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </footer>

  <nav class="about-actions" aria-label="{{ site.meditationNav }}">
    <a href="{{ '/' | url }}">Today's meditation</a>
    <a href="{{ '/index/' | url }}">{{ site.meditationsIndex }}</a>
  </nav>
</article>
